### Create a new topic
POST http://localhost:8080/api/topics
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Java Programming",
  "description": "Basic Java programming concepts"
}

### Get all topics
GET http://localhost:8080/api/topics

### Get a specific topic
GET http://localhost:8080/api/topics/1

### Generate questions
POST http://localhost:8080/api/questions/generate
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "topicId": 1,
  "difficultyLevel": "BEGINNER",
  "count": 3
}

### Get questions by topic
GET http://localhost:8080/api/questions/topic/1?difficulty=BEGINNER

### Get questions by difficulty
GET http://localhost:8080/api/questions/difficulty/INTERMEDIATE

### Add a manual question
POST http://localhost:8080/api/questions/topic/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "question": "What is the main purpose of the 'public static void main(String[] args)' method in Java?",
  "options": [
    "To declare a variable",
    "To create a new class",
    "To serve as the entry point of a Java program",
    "To import packages"
  ],
  "correctAnswer": "To serve as the entry point of a Java program",
  "explanation": "The main method serves as the entry point for Java applications. When you run a Java program, the JVM looks for this method to begin program execution.",
  "difficultyLevel": "BEGINNER"
} 